Rating: 4
I just made this coffee cake over the weekend and it was wonderful. After reading the reviews, I baked in a bunt pan for 55 minutes at 375 F. I used fresh blueberries and floured the blueberries in the bottom layers. I greased and floured the pan. I layered the topping in the bottom. I substituted 1 cup of chopped walnuts for the coconut. Next I layered a portion of the blueberries. Followed by about 1/2 the batter. About half of the remaining blueberries, then the rest of the batter followed by the remaining blueberries. I made the following changes to the batter: I used 1/2 cup sugar and 6 tablespoons of butter. I added 2 tbsp of lemon juice and 1 tsp of vanilla to the batter. I also happened to have buttermilk on hand and substituted that for the milk. It came out great, but note the cake is crumbly and it will break easily. Everyone that has had it loved it.

