Rating: 3
This is terrific! I've made it twice, and every loved it both times. Folks: Why are the words frozen and unthawed difficult to understand? It's two ways of saying the same thing. The berries are to be frozen; do not thaw them. If you've ever made anything from thawed blueberries (berries that have been frozen and are now thawed, you know that it turns the batter blue. That effect is lessened if you leave them frozen. Once you start cooking a bit more that will become something you read very often. Hopefully it worked out ok for you - - this recipe is really good.

